                            <comment id="14292883" author="cleartplinkminute" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 02:42:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Full command I ran:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;../mahout-distribution-0.9/bin/mahout streamingkmeans -i ../vdb_artifacts/mahout_vectors.data -o cluster_data -k 500 -ow -dm org.apache.mahout.common.distance.CosineDistanceMeasure 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14292901" author="smarthi" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 03:00:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The error is due to not specifying the parameter &quot;estimatedNumMapClusters&quot;  via -km parameter. See &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17272296/how-to-use-mahout-streaming-k-means/18090471#18090471&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17272296/how-to-use-mahout-streaming-k-means/18090471#18090471&lt;/a&gt; for instructions on how to run this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, CosineDistanceMeasure wouldn&apos;t be appropriate for K-Means, its gotta be a SquaredEuclideanDistance. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14292905" author="cleartplinkminute" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 03:04:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s correct Suneel; as I specifically stated in both the first line of the bug, and the title, the error is indeed due to not specifying -km.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug that I&apos;m reporting is that this isn&apos;t checked and caught by the CLI.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14292906" author="cleartplinkminute" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 03:04:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue hasn&apos;t magically fixed the fact that this required parameter is not validated as required by the CLI. Reopening it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14292912" author="smarthi" created="Tue, 27 Jan 2015 03:14:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops, my bad for not reading the jira entirely and just looking at the stacktrace. Thanks for reopening.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
